Method Detail

put

public Binding put(ConverterType converterType,
                   Binding binding)
Validates the converter type and the binding (using validatePut) before insertion, throwing an exception if a problem is found.

In particular, bindings cannot be overwritten; they must be specifically removed from this map before a new put operation with the given converter type can be done.

Specified by:
put in interface Map<ConverterType,Binding>
Overrides:
put in class HashMap<ConverterType,Binding>
Returns:
null if there was no previous binding for converterType, or binding if it was already associated with converterType.
Throws:
RuntimeException - all exceptions thrown by validatePut(ConverterType, Binding).
See Also:
validatePut(ConverterType, Binding)

validatePut

protected boolean validatePut(ConverterType converterType,
                              Binding binding)
Checks if the converter type and the binding can be stored in this map.

The restrictions implemented here are:

  • neither converterType nor binding can be null.
  • a converter type must be obtainable from binding.
  • converterType must be assignable from binding's converter type.
  • this map must not have converterType associated to a binding other than binding.

Parameters:
converterType - a converter type.
binding - a binding.
Returns:
true if converterType is already associated with binding, or false if converterType is not associated to a binding here.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if either converterType or binding are null.
ConverterTypeIncompatibleWithBindingException - if converterType and binding are not compatible.
ConverterTypeInstantiationException - if a converter type cannot be obtained from binding.
ConverterCollisionException - if this map already has a different binding associated to converterType.
See Also:
checkForCompatibility(ConverterType, Binding), checkForCollision(ConverterType, Binding)

checkForCompatibility

protected void checkForCompatibility(ConverterType converterType,
                                     Binding binding)
                              throws ConverterTypeIncompatibleWithBindingException
Checks if the converter type and the binding are mutually compatible.

The restrictions are:

  • neither converterType nor binding can be null.
  • a converter type must be obtainable using binding.
  • converterType must be assignable from binding's converter type.

Parameters:
converterType - a converter type.
binding - a binding.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if either converterType or binding are null.
ConverterTypeIncompatibleWithBindingException - if converterType and binding are not compatible.
ConverterTypeInstantiationException - if binding cannot be used to extract a converter type.
See Also:
ConverterType.fromBinding(Binding), ConverterType.isAssignableFrom(ConverterType)

Checks if the converter type and the binding can be stored in the map.

The restrictions are:

  • neither converterType nor binding nor map can be null.
  • map must not have converterType associated to a binding different than binding.

Parameters:

binding - a binding.
map - a map.
Returns:

Throws:

putAll

public void putAll(Map<? extends ConverterType,? extends Binding> map)
Attempts to add the bindings in the given map to this map, doing nothing if the given map is null or empty. All entries are validated before actual insertion.
